{"TopicId":169198,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Accindentally rotated craft away from vertical in the VAB","CreatedByName":"CosmicCharlie","CreatedById":150762,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-03T20:26:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"CosmicCharlie","CreatedById":150762,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-03T20:26:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeen trying for a half hour to get it back to vertical. Is there a trick?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Plusck","CreatedById":153264,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-03T20:55:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA few tricks:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- the rotate gizmo can be either relative or absolute. If you have something rotated to an odd angle, toggle to absolute and rotate it back. Default key is \u0022F\u0022 I think.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo just select your root part and use the rotate gizmo on it for the whole ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- if picking up your root part and rotating with the W-A-S-D-Q-or-E keys doesn\u0027t work, try getting it close and using shift-WASDQE for smaller angles\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- change your root part to another root part, grab it and use WASDQE again as necessary.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-01-03T20:56:25Z\u0022 title=\u002201/03/2018 08:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 3, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Plusck\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CosmicCharlie","CreatedById":150762,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-04T04:33:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks much.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-04T05:35:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, picking up a part and pressing space will reset its rotation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Plusck","CreatedById":153264,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-04T17:48:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223259338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022169198\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221515044152\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, picking up a part and pressing space will reset its rotation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncool - never even knew that was possible \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-01-04T17:48:25Z\u0022 title=\u002201/04/2018 05:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 4, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Plusck\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}